.TH "gfs2_adjust_reservation" 9 "gfs2_adjust_reservation" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gfs2_adjust_reservation \- Adjust (or remove) a reservation after allocation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" gfs2_adjust_reservation
.BI "(struct gfs2_inode *ip "  ","
.BI "const struct gfs2_rbm *rbm "  ","
.BI "unsigned len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ip" 12
The inode we have just allocated blocks for
.IP "rbm" 12
The start of the allocated blocks
.IP "len" 12
The extent length
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Adjusts a reservation after an allocation has taken place. If the
reservation does not match the allocation, or if it is now empty
then it is removed.
